2023 Graduate Speaker

Damian Cole Manwarren

Damian Manwarren is an exceptional student. Later this month, Damian will have earned his High School Diploma from O’Fallon Township High School, moreover; this evening he is graduating with his Associates in Arts and Associates in Science.

Damian spent his two last years in the Running Start program which allowed him to attend Southwestern Illinois College full-time while simultaneously achieving his academic high school requirements. Outside of his dedication to his academics, Damian enjoys horseback riding, martial arts, hiking, and camping.

His dream is to become the first doctor in his family. Damian is going to begin a new journey in the Fall studying Pre-Med at Washington University in St. Louis. Damian is the proud son of Ms. Sarah Schwartz.

Photography Policy

Please remain seated during the ceremony, except when you are receiving your diploma scroll.

Leaving your seat may interfere with the ceremony.

A professional photographer from GradImages will take photos during the Commencement.

To order copies of these photos, visit www.gradimages.com or call 800-261-2576.

Congratulations Class of 2022-2023!

Don’t forget to submit your custom announcement using the Graduation Submission form.

Your custom announcements will be linked to your name below.

Foundation

The Southwestern Illinois College Foundation exists to maintain and enhance the quality of life by developing friends and funds for support of the educational, cultural and service goals of Southwestern Illinois College.

The Foundation promotes excellence by securing gifts for special educational and

cultural activities that are not part of the college budget.

MISSION

Southwestern Illinois College upholds the dignity and worth of students, employees and community, which empowers learning and enhances the quality of life.

VISION

To be students’ first choice by providing innovative and flexible programs designed to enrich our

community and foster economic growth in our region.
